# Project: Thriven Step Sequencer

A browser-based step sequencer / beat-maker (Milo-style) for Tekk / RaveTekk / Deep Tekk
production. Built by SiCKaRiM (Karim), Frankfurt. Will later be packaged as an offline
desktop app via Tauri.

## Communication
- Talk to me (the user) in GERMAN. Be direct, factual, concise. No filler, no flattery.
- All CODE, COMMENTS, variable names, commit messages: ENGLISH.
- I am a self-taught developer (JS/TS/Python). Explain non-obvious decisions briefly so I learn.

## Tech Stack
- Vite + Vanilla TypeScript (NO React/framework for now — keep it lean)
- Tone.js for all audio: Tone.Transport, Tone.Sequence, synths, effects
- Web MIDI API for live output to hardware (Akai MPD24)
- Standard MIDI File export (hand-written or midi-writer-js)
- Tauri (Rust) only in a later phase — do not add it yet

## Code Conventions
- TypeScript strict mode. Never use `any` — use `unknown` or a defined type.
- Named exports only, no default exports.
- Small focused modules under src/{audio,sequencer,ui,midi}/.
- Arrow-function consts for handlers. Async code must handle errors (try/catch).
- No external dependency unless necessary — budget is 0€, offline-first, free/self-hosted only.
- Do not rely on localStorage in artifacts/preview; use in-memory state.

## Domain Model (keep consistent)
- Pattern: tracks[] × steps[16]; each step = { on, prob, tie }.
- prob = 50% trigger chance. tie = roll (extra hit at +1/32).
- Patches A–J = 10 pattern slots, reused as song sections in the SC (Song Chain) view.
- Three views: SEQ (sequencer), MIX (16-ch mixer), SC (arrangement).
- Default tempo 162 BPM. Tekk kick on steps 1,5,9,13 (0-indexed 0,4,8,12).

## Aesthetic
- Dark UI, neon accents (cyan #00f0ff, magenta #ff2bd6) on near-black (#07080c).
- Display font: Chakra Petch. Mono body: JetBrains Mono. No generic fonts (Inter/Arial).

## Output Rules
- Code must be copy-paste-ready, complete, no placeholders like "// TODO rest here".
- When unsure about a Tone.js API, say so — do not invent method names.
- Use the reference/thriven-step-seq.html as a behavioral reference, but write clean modular TS.
